	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64560313"><p>"I'm sure they could occupy it."</p><p>Maybe, maybe not. So far space stations have been little more than metaphorical flag planting by the countries concerned though they justify them with some frankly risible "science". There's zero political capital to be gained for country to rent some habitat from Musk and its unlikely many commercial ventures would want or need it either unless some amazing new tech comes along that can only be developed in microgravity.</p></div>
